1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:04,169
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:04,171 --> 00:00:06,171
<i>At least it used to be,</i>

3
00:00:06,173 --> 00:00:08,173
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:08,175 --> 00:00:10,242
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:14,015 --> 00:00:16,482
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:16,484 --> 00:00:18,250
<i>And completely inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:18,252 --> 00:00:20,252
We're trapped.

8
00:00:20,254 --> 00:00:22,721
Julia:
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:22,723 --> 00:00:25,224
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:25,226 --> 00:00:27,292
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:27,294 --> 00:00:28,794
I know, junior.

12
00:00:28,796 --> 00:00:30,195
What are you talking about?

13
00:00:30,197 --> 00:00:31,563
About angie.

14
00:00:31,565 --> 00:00:34,199
Hello?

15
00:00:36,337 --> 00:00:38,704
Nobody's gonna
follow you anywhere,

16
00:00:38,706 --> 00:00:42,074
Ever, when they hear just
exactly who you are.

17
00:00:43,543 --> 00:00:46,378
The military plans
to launch a powerful missile

18
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:47,746
In the hopes
of destroying the dome.

19
00:00:47,748 --> 00:00:50,349
All right, everybody, stay put,
and remain calm!

20
00:01:06,332 --> 00:01:08,500
I can't believe it.

21
00:01:08,502 --> 00:01:10,436
The dome's still here.

22
00:01:10,438 --> 00:01:13,405
Good thing they
evacuated everyone outside.

23
00:01:18,545 --> 00:01:21,814
Hey, you guys okay?

24
00:01:21,816 --> 00:01:23,282
We saw the missile
hit the dome.

25
00:01:24,285 --> 00:01:25,717
Didn't even put a dent in it.

26
00:01:25,719 --> 00:01:29,388
Grinnell:
What's it made of
if a bomb couldn't blow it up?

27
00:01:29,390 --> 00:01:31,390
She's right.
How is that possible?

28
00:01:31,392 --> 00:01:33,659
I don't know.

29
00:01:33,661 --> 00:01:35,727
Nothing about this thing
makes any sense.

30
00:01:35,729 --> 00:01:37,362
You can say that again.

31
00:01:37,364 --> 00:01:39,298
Still smooth as a baby's butt.

32
00:01:39,300 --> 00:01:41,500
Big jim:
Stay back!

33
00:01:41,502 --> 00:01:42,701
Stay back, everyone!

34
00:01:42,703 --> 00:01:44,436
Remember sheriff perkins.

35
00:01:44,438 --> 00:01:47,239
Touching that thing exploded
his damn pacemaker.

36
00:01:47,241 --> 00:01:48,474
Norrie?

37
00:01:49,242 --> 00:01:50,476
Mom!

38
00:01:50,478 --> 00:01:52,377
Honey, honey.

39
00:01:52,379 --> 00:01:54,379
Oh, god, are you okay?

40
00:01:54,381 --> 00:01:56,315
I'm sorry I ran off.
Oh.

41
00:01:56,317 --> 00:01:58,450
If anything had
happened to you...

42
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:01,386
Linda?

43
00:02:01,388 --> 00:02:02,688
Where are
your deputies?

44
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:04,490
Well, who do you think
I'm trying to find?

45
00:02:04,492 --> 00:02:08,327
He didn't evacuate to
the factory with everyone else.

46
00:02:08,329 --> 00:02:10,562
Yeah, I'm looking for him
myself, but he's a big boy.

47
00:02:10,564 --> 00:02:12,331
He can handle himself.

48
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:14,633
I wish I could say the
same for reverend coggins.

49
00:02:14,635 --> 00:02:17,836
Carter found his body by the
dome where we had visitors' day.

50
00:02:17,838 --> 00:02:21,173
Good lord.

51
00:02:21,175 --> 00:02:22,508
Coggins is dead?

52
00:02:22,510 --> 00:02:24,276
His hearing
aid exploded.

53
00:02:24,278 --> 00:02:26,645
He must have touched the
dome, and it just fried him.

54
00:02:26,647 --> 00:02:30,282
Ollie:
First duke, now
the reverend?

55
00:02:30,284 --> 00:02:32,317
Well, how many more of us
is this thing gonna kill?

56
00:02:32,319 --> 00:02:34,453
Just take it easy, ollie.
You're scaring people, okay?

57
00:02:34,455 --> 00:02:36,522
Well, it's a little too late
for that now.

58
00:02:36,524 --> 00:02:40,526
We've all banded together
before, and we survived, okay?

59
00:02:40,528 --> 00:02:41,493
Grinnell:
Yeah, until we run

60
00:02:41,495 --> 00:02:43,228
Out of food in here.

61
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:45,230
How about electricity?
I'm nearly out of propane.

62
00:02:45,232 --> 00:02:48,400
Been warming up canned
soup in my fireplace.

63
00:02:48,402 --> 00:02:51,336
I suggest we take this
to a town hall meeting. We...

64
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:53,672
What, so you can keep jawing
while more people die?

65
00:02:53,674 --> 00:02:55,674
Hey, my jawing's gotten us
through plenty, ollie.

66
00:02:55,676 --> 00:02:56,909
Now, why don't you help

67
00:02:56,911 --> 00:02:58,510
By keeping your damn head
on straight?

68
00:02:58,512 --> 00:03:00,445
Can we please just
get out of here?

69
00:03:00,447 --> 00:03:02,581
Yeah, before a
fight breaks out.

70
00:03:02,583 --> 00:03:04,616
It's, like,
a hundred degrees today.

71
00:03:04,618 --> 00:03:07,719
Let's get back to the car.

72
00:03:07,721 --> 00:03:09,588
Joe, you can come with us.

73
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:14,726
Honestly, I'm a little scared.

74
00:03:17,497 --> 00:03:19,398
What happens
when we run out of everything?

75
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,867
What do we do then?

76
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,939
I don't know.

77
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:32,477
The walkies aren't working.

78
00:03:35,249 --> 00:03:36,415
I can't get a frequency.

79
00:03:36,417 --> 00:03:38,483
hey,

80
00:03:38,485 --> 00:03:41,520
Barbie, till I can
reach my deputies...

81
00:03:41,522 --> 00:03:44,356
I'm gonna need another hand.

82
00:03:45,425 --> 00:03:48,760
I'll help you,
but I don't need your badge.

83
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,666
We can talk about
how this will work.

84
00:03:54,668 --> 00:03:55,834
Julia:
I'm gonna head over

85
00:03:55,836 --> 00:03:59,504
See if they're picking
anything up from the outside.

86
00:03:59,506 --> 00:04:02,474
I'll see you later?

87
00:04:02,476 --> 00:04:04,409
Yeah. Okay.

88
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:06,445
Ollie:
You know what
this means, folks?

89
00:04:06,447 --> 00:04:07,713
We're never getting
out of here.

90
00:04:07,715 --> 00:04:09,915
Ollie, at least you have
a farm to feed yourself.

91
00:04:09,917 --> 00:04:11,817
what about the rest of us?

92
00:04:11,819 --> 00:04:13,619
Big jim:
You have my word, people!

93
00:04:13,621 --> 00:04:16,288
No one's gonna starve
in chester's mill.

94
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:23,895
It's crazy.

95
00:04:23,897 --> 00:04:26,531
Five minutes ago,
I thought we were gonna die.

96
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:32,971
It's worse
not knowing what's next.

97
00:04:32,973 --> 00:04:34,906
You don't need
to be scared, angie.

98
00:04:37,910 --> 00:04:40,846
Didn't you notice
I'm a deputy now?

99
00:04:40,848 --> 00:04:42,981
People trust me,

100
00:04:42,983 --> 00:04:45,684
Just like you should.

101
00:04:48,521 --> 00:04:52,457
Whatever happens,
I'll take care of you.

102
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,034
Angie, don't do this!

103
00:05:02,036 --> 00:05:03,368
Angie!

104
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:05,070
angie!

105
00:05:05,072 --> 00:05:07,039
Alice:
Just let me out of the car.

106
00:05:07,041 --> 00:05:08,874
Let me out of the car.

107
00:05:10,878 --> 00:05:12,911
Why'd you make me
stop? What's wrong?

108
00:05:12,913 --> 00:05:15,414
I just... I need some air.

109
00:05:15,416 --> 00:05:17,616
It's boiling hot in there.

110
00:05:17,618 --> 00:05:19,685
Mom, are you okay?
She-she's fine.

111
00:05:19,687 --> 00:05:21,920
Alice, just get
back in the car.

112
00:05:21,922 --> 00:05:23,622
I'll blast the ac.

113
00:05:23,624 --> 00:05:25,390
What time's our flight?

114
00:05:25,392 --> 00:05:26,858
What flight?

115
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:28,894
To l.A.
I don't want to miss it.

116
00:05:28,896 --> 00:05:30,529
Norrie:
Mom, watch out!

117
00:05:48,481 --> 00:05:51,350
Oh, my god!

118
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:55,087
Are you okay?

119
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:33,792
Is everybody okay?

120
00:06:33,794 --> 00:06:36,128
What happened?

121
00:06:36,130 --> 00:06:38,597
Alice didn't see
the truck coming.

122
00:06:38,599 --> 00:06:39,931
The driver swerved
and hit the tower.

123
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:42,100
Joe and norrie pulled him out
just in time.

124
00:06:42,102 --> 00:06:45,470
Hey. Oh, got him.
Good job, you guys.

125
00:06:49,442 --> 00:06:50,842
The pipe's a goner.

126
00:06:50,844 --> 00:06:53,612
Where's your tower
get its water from?

127
00:06:53,614 --> 00:06:54,846
Lake eastpointe.

128
00:06:54,848 --> 00:06:57,015
It's our main source.

129
00:06:57,017 --> 00:06:58,817
All right, well,
we'll haul water from there.

130
00:06:58,819 --> 00:07:00,886
In the meantime,
we should check it out.

131
00:07:04,524 --> 00:07:06,658
Okay, look-look at me,
look at me.

132
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:08,593
Alice, when's the last time
you took your insulin?

133
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:10,195
I ran out.

134
00:07:10,197 --> 00:07:12,564
With the bomb craziness
and everything, I just...

135
00:07:12,566 --> 00:07:13,932
I lost track.

136
00:07:13,934 --> 00:07:16,701
Come on, we got to get you
to the clinic right now.

137
00:07:16,703 --> 00:07:18,470
Okay?

138
00:07:19,705 --> 00:07:21,206
What's wrong
with your mom?

139
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:23,074
She's a diabetic.

140
00:07:23,076 --> 00:07:26,011
Kind of loses it when
she forgets to take her insulin.

141
00:07:33,053 --> 00:07:35,053
What is that noise?
I don't know,

142
00:07:35,055 --> 00:07:36,555
But it's jamming our broadcast.

143
00:07:36,557 --> 00:07:38,623
Kind of sounds like the alien
from <i>aliens.</i>

144
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:41,493
Well, all the police walkies
are making the same sound.

145
00:07:41,495 --> 00:07:43,495
Is dodee picking up
any military chatter

146
00:07:43,497 --> 00:07:44,663
From outside the dome?

147
00:07:44,665 --> 00:07:46,798
Oh, screech is
jamming that, too.

148
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:50,802
And if it's this loud, then
the source is probably close.

149
00:07:50,804 --> 00:07:52,103
How close?

150
00:07:52,105 --> 00:07:54,539
Best guess? Mile or two.

151
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:56,007
So it's inside chester's mill?

152
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:03,682
Listen, if it's that close,
maybe we can find it.

153
00:08:03,684 --> 00:08:05,817
Dodee:
One step ahead
of you, julia.

154
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:11,723
Do I even want
to know what that is?

155
00:08:11,725 --> 00:08:13,592
Us radio heads call it a "yagi."

156
00:08:13,594 --> 00:08:15,794
I rigged it to locate
the source of the screech

157
00:08:15,796 --> 00:08:18,530
Using frequency triangulation.

158
00:08:18,532 --> 00:08:20,632
Look, whatever
this screech is,

159
00:08:20,634 --> 00:08:22,267
It can't be a coincidence
that it started

160
00:08:22,269 --> 00:08:24,669
Just as the missile
was about to hit the dome.

161
00:08:24,671 --> 00:08:26,805
You think the dome
was trying to scream?

162
00:08:26,807 --> 00:08:27,973
Or protect itself.

163
00:08:27,975 --> 00:08:29,608
Dodee:
Who knows?

164
00:08:29,610 --> 00:08:32,844
It might be what's generating
the dome itself.

165
00:08:32,846 --> 00:08:36,648
We just have to follow
the signal to the power source.

166
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:40,519
Well, if that's true,
then if we can track it down...

167
00:08:40,521 --> 00:08:43,755
Maybe we can turn it off.

168
00:08:45,725 --> 00:08:49,828
It's none of my business,
but you're lucky to have her.

169
00:08:49,830 --> 00:08:51,897
Her?

170
00:08:51,899 --> 00:08:54,666
I have eyes, you know.

171
00:08:54,668 --> 00:08:57,669
Oh, julia and I
aren't exactly an item.

172
00:08:57,671 --> 00:09:01,606
Well, from the sparks that
I saw flying, you should be.

173
00:09:03,109 --> 00:09:06,278
I'd kill to have
rusty back right now.

174
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:08,313
How long you two
been together?

175
00:09:08,315 --> 00:09:10,048
Three years.

176
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:12,050
We're supposed
to get married next month.

177
00:09:12,052 --> 00:09:15,253
But now it just seems
like some dream I made up.

178
00:09:20,826 --> 00:09:22,594
What the hell?

179
00:09:31,203 --> 00:09:32,737
You can't be out.

180
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:34,773
I was just here the other day.

181
00:09:34,775 --> 00:09:36,575
You had insulin.

182
00:09:36,577 --> 00:09:38,877
We have 23 diabetics
in chester's mill.

183
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:41,947
Our insulin
supply is gone.

184
00:09:41,949 --> 00:09:44,149
Pharmacy has to have some.

185
00:09:44,151 --> 00:09:46,117
When reverend coggins
ransacked the place,

186
00:09:46,119 --> 00:09:49,087
He took all of the drugs,
including the insulin.

187
00:09:50,656 --> 00:09:53,892
What are we supposed to do?

188
00:09:55,795 --> 00:09:57,362
Pray.

189
00:10:02,835 --> 00:10:04,836
Jim, we have a situation.

190
00:10:04,838 --> 00:10:07,172
The water tower...
Yeah, I know; it fell.

191
00:10:07,174 --> 00:10:09,975
We'll just have to get our water
from lake eastpointe.

192
00:10:09,977 --> 00:10:11,042
Can't.

193
00:10:14,981 --> 00:10:16,715
What are you doing?

194
00:10:23,255 --> 00:10:25,724
This is the water from the lake.

195
00:10:25,726 --> 00:10:27,092
It's polluted with methane.

196
00:10:27,094 --> 00:10:28,893
Must've cut through
an underground mineral pocket

197
00:10:28,895 --> 00:10:30,095
When the dome came down.

198
00:10:30,097 --> 00:10:32,197
So it's undrinkable.

199
00:10:32,199 --> 00:10:34,699
Yeah, until we figure out
how to filter it.

200
00:10:34,701 --> 00:10:37,002
What about rain?

201
00:10:37,004 --> 00:10:39,871
Is that dome high enough
for storm clouds to form?

202
00:10:39,873 --> 00:10:41,640
I have no idea.

203
00:10:41,642 --> 00:10:44,709
You know, not too many people
take the time

204
00:10:44,711 --> 00:10:46,911
To get to know their town.

205
00:10:46,913 --> 00:10:49,080
A shame, really.

206
00:10:49,082 --> 00:10:50,882
There's history here.

207
00:10:50,884 --> 00:10:53,218
Right in our
own backyards.

208
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:56,287
My grandfather gave me this map
when I was a kid.

209
00:10:56,289 --> 00:10:58,757
I used to spend hours
poring over it,

210
00:10:58,759 --> 00:11:01,026
Learning the lay of the land.

211
00:11:01,028 --> 00:11:04,095
There are artesian wells
underneath chester's mill.

212
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:07,232
You know, some have dried
up by now, but, uh...

213
00:11:07,234 --> 00:11:10,301
This one here is
still flowing strongly.

214
00:11:10,303 --> 00:11:13,672
It's right under ollie
densmore's place.

215
00:11:13,674 --> 00:11:16,141
And I'm guessing
he owns the rights.

216
00:11:16,143 --> 00:11:17,809
We have to go see him.
No, no, no, no.

217
00:11:17,811 --> 00:11:21,413
That he can be a pain
in the ass, so...

218
00:11:21,415 --> 00:11:23,982
I'll go talk to him.

219
00:11:33,893 --> 00:11:35,860
Dad.

220
00:11:35,862 --> 00:11:37,996
Where you been?
You okay?

221
00:11:37,998 --> 00:11:40,031
I can't find angie.

222
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:41,132
She's gone.

223
00:11:41,134 --> 00:11:42,934
Was she with you
when the bomb went off?

224
00:11:42,936 --> 00:11:45,970
Yeah, but she... Got away.

225
00:11:45,972 --> 00:11:47,305
Well, then find her.
If she opens her mouth

226
00:11:47,307 --> 00:11:48,306
About being locked up...
Wait.

227
00:11:48,308 --> 00:11:49,841
Wait a minute.

228
00:11:49,843 --> 00:11:51,876
Now, I've been
looking for her.

229
00:11:51,878 --> 00:11:54,813
Besides, you're the
one who let her go.

230
00:11:54,815 --> 00:11:56,948
Damn it. Don't you put this
on me, junior.

231
00:11:56,950 --> 00:11:58,083
This is your mess.

232
00:11:58,085 --> 00:12:00,085
And right now,
I got one of my own.

233
00:12:00,087 --> 00:12:02,153
So for once in your life,
do your own damage control.

234
00:12:02,155 --> 00:12:03,988
Get out there
and find that girl.

235
00:12:10,296 --> 00:12:13,965
Hey, so how long has big
jim known ollie densmore?

236
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:16,367
Way duke told it,
all their lives.

237
00:12:16,369 --> 00:12:18,369
Jim and ollie
would be friends one day

238
00:12:18,371 --> 00:12:20,038
And then enemies the next.

239
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:22,507
They'd patch it up over a
burger at sweetbriar, but...

240
00:12:22,509 --> 00:12:23,842
They'd be fighting
about something new

241
00:12:23,844 --> 00:12:25,510
The following week.

242
00:12:25,512 --> 00:12:28,446
And speaking of fighting, we
should probably check this out.

243
00:12:32,785 --> 00:12:35,987
Folks, listen, I'm sorry, but
the only payment I can accept

244
00:12:35,989 --> 00:12:38,957
Is either propane or batteries.
Man: So our money's
no good now?

245
00:12:38,959 --> 00:12:40,291
I mean, we got cash.

246
00:12:40,293 --> 00:12:42,994
And we've been waiting
out here forever.

247
00:12:42,996 --> 00:12:45,096
Terry, what's going on here?

248
00:12:45,098 --> 00:12:48,299
I'm just trying to explain the
new reality to these people.

249
00:12:48,301 --> 00:12:50,034
Look, I can't
feed my family

250
00:12:50,036 --> 00:12:52,003
With money no one's
gonna take.

251
00:12:52,005 --> 00:12:53,238
Man:
New reality?

252
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:55,240
Sounds like
a scam to me.

253
00:12:55,242 --> 00:12:57,375
I'm not trying to...
Hey, come on,
guys, come on.

254
00:12:57,377 --> 00:12:59,144
Is it true
the lake is ruined?

255
00:12:59,146 --> 00:13:00,945
I hear we're gonna
run out of water.

256
00:13:00,947 --> 00:13:04,015
Starting a panic
is not gonna help anyone.

257
00:13:04,017 --> 00:13:05,850
All right? So, does
anybody here have batteries

258
00:13:05,852 --> 00:13:07,986
That we can loan to dres?

259
00:13:07,988 --> 00:13:09,921
Anybody?

260
00:13:12,091 --> 00:13:14,492
Thank you.

261
00:13:14,494 --> 00:13:16,261
There's no need for alarm.

262
00:13:16,263 --> 00:13:18,396
I'm sorry
for making a scene.

263
00:13:18,398 --> 00:13:20,965
Thank you,
sheriff.

264
00:13:20,967 --> 00:13:22,967
Barbie:
You really believe that?

265
00:13:22,969 --> 00:13:27,939
You always believe in the
goodness of people you serve.

266
00:13:27,941 --> 00:13:30,508
That's what duke taught me
on the first day of the job.

267
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:32,510
Yeah, and if
they prove you wrong?

268
00:13:32,512 --> 00:13:34,579
Rule number two...

269
00:13:37,349 --> 00:13:40,051
...You do what you got to do.

270
00:13:40,053 --> 00:13:41,986
That's not a good idea.

271
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:43,588
Why?

272
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:46,825
I mean, didn't you have a gun
when you chased after randolph?

273
00:13:46,827 --> 00:13:49,294
Yeah, but randolph
killed freddy.

274
00:13:49,296 --> 00:13:50,995
These people...

275
00:13:52,499 --> 00:13:54,833
...These people are scared.

276
00:13:59,371 --> 00:14:02,106
To tell you the truth...

277
00:14:02,108 --> 00:14:04,075
So am I.

278
00:14:09,582 --> 00:14:12,317
Ollie! Hey!

279
00:14:12,319 --> 00:14:14,586
Won't take up
too much of your time.

280
00:14:14,588 --> 00:14:17,088
All the time in the world
for you, big jim.

281
00:14:17,090 --> 00:14:19,457
We got a water problem.
That concerns me,

282
00:14:19,459 --> 00:14:22,193
Uh... How?

283
00:14:22,195 --> 00:14:26,564
And the people of chester's mill
could really use your help.

284
00:14:26,566 --> 00:14:28,499
What's in it for me?

285
00:14:28,501 --> 00:14:31,436
How about a sense
of civic pride?

286
00:14:31,438 --> 00:14:33,504
That's typical.

287
00:14:33,506 --> 00:14:36,074
You always take me
for granted, jim.

288
00:14:36,076 --> 00:14:37,976
All us farmers.

289
00:14:37,978 --> 00:14:40,445
Till now.
You still sore
the town council

290
00:14:40,447 --> 00:14:42,513
Took kip lester's side
on that fence dispute?

291
00:14:42,515 --> 00:14:46,417
That so-called "fence dispute"
lost me seven acres of my farm.

292
00:14:46,419 --> 00:14:48,386
That was 15 years ago, ollie.

293
00:14:48,388 --> 00:14:49,888
Well, that's
a drop in the bucket

294
00:14:49,890 --> 00:14:51,589
Compared to how long
you and me go back.

295
00:14:51,591 --> 00:14:53,591
I figured I could've
counted on you.

296
00:14:53,593 --> 00:14:55,460
You know the law
tied my hands on that.

297
00:14:55,462 --> 00:14:57,595
Like that's stopped you
before now.

298
00:14:57,597 --> 00:14:59,163
Damn it, be reasonable, ollie.

299
00:14:59,165 --> 00:15:00,999
That's exactly what I'm being.

300
00:15:01,001 --> 00:15:04,469
You want my water,
you'll have to pay for it.

301
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:08,172
Today at the dome,
you were talking about

302
00:15:08,174 --> 00:15:09,540
Running low on propane.

303
00:15:09,542 --> 00:15:11,342
You know, the
propane it takes

304
00:15:11,344 --> 00:15:14,345
To run your irrigation system
and light your house.

305
00:15:14,347 --> 00:15:15,647
L-let me guess.

306
00:15:15,649 --> 00:15:17,415
You have some.

307
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:18,917
Plenty.

308
00:15:18,919 --> 00:15:21,219
Why am I not surprised
big jim rennie

309
00:15:21,221 --> 00:15:23,454
Just happens to have
what chester's mill needs

310
00:15:23,456 --> 00:15:25,223
In its moment of crisis?

311
00:15:25,225 --> 00:15:26,624
It's nothing sinister, ollie.

312
00:15:26,626 --> 00:15:29,560
Town keeps a reserve
in case of emergency.

313
00:15:29,562 --> 00:15:34,365
You get me propane,
town gets its water.

314
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:53,151
Carter: Just in time.
Things getting out of control?

315
00:15:53,153 --> 00:15:54,619
Not yet, but the
mood's pretty ugly.

316
00:15:54,621 --> 00:15:56,721
Barbie, get inside
and keep peace at the register.

317
00:15:56,723 --> 00:15:58,990
Carter, slow the flow
of people going inside.

318
00:16:02,595 --> 00:16:05,730
Where have you been
all morning?
Sorry, linda,

319
00:16:05,732 --> 00:16:08,232
I got a situation
I need to take care of.

320
00:16:08,234 --> 00:16:09,233
I'm looking for someone.

321
00:16:09,235 --> 00:16:10,702
Well, I need you
to do your job.

322
00:16:10,704 --> 00:16:13,338
Man: You can let more people
in your store. Come on!

323
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:15,206
Ladies and gentlemen,
due to demand,

324
00:16:15,208 --> 00:16:18,109
We are now limiting each
customer's purchase to a total

325
00:16:18,111 --> 00:16:20,244
Of two liters
of water.

326
00:16:20,246 --> 00:16:21,612
Work the aisles.

327
00:16:21,614 --> 00:16:24,315
Just keep smiling,
and... Stay alert.

328
00:16:26,752 --> 00:16:30,455
Junior:
Waylon, clint, hold it.

329
00:16:32,191 --> 00:16:34,592
Isn't this cute;
little big jim playing cop.

330
00:16:34,594 --> 00:16:36,694
Drop those and step back.

331
00:16:36,696 --> 00:16:38,463
Or what? You gonna
teach us a lesson?

332
00:16:38,465 --> 00:16:40,298
If I have to.

333
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:42,633
Hey, uh, come on.
Are you serious?

334
00:16:42,635 --> 00:16:44,369
Hey! I was here first!
Ida...

335
00:16:44,371 --> 00:16:46,104
My son is sick;
I need this!

336
00:16:46,106 --> 00:16:47,538
I don't care!
Hey, hey, come on, ladies.

337
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:50,074
hey, knock it off.
Knock it off.

338
00:16:50,076 --> 00:16:52,744
Joe, what am I
going to do?

339
00:16:52,746 --> 00:16:56,014
I can't just
let my mom die.

340
00:16:57,649 --> 00:17:00,151
Not like this.

341
00:17:00,153 --> 00:17:02,787
Tell me how to help.

342
00:17:02,789 --> 00:17:05,456
I'll do anything.

343
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:10,395
Wh-where are you going?
The nurse said that

344
00:17:10,397 --> 00:17:12,063
There's a bunch of
other diabetics in town.

345
00:17:12,065 --> 00:17:13,698
Their files have to be
in here somewhere.

346
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,133
Okay, you think
people are just gonna

347
00:17:15,135 --> 00:17:16,567
Give you their insulin
if you ask?

348
00:17:16,569 --> 00:17:18,169
Who said I was
gonna ask?
N-norrie...

349
00:17:18,171 --> 00:17:19,604
If you don't like
it, don't come.

350
00:17:19,606 --> 00:17:23,474
Julia: <i>Are we getting closer</i>
<i>to the signal?</i>

351
00:17:23,476 --> 00:17:26,044
no.

352
00:17:26,046 --> 00:17:27,812
What?

353
00:17:27,814 --> 00:17:29,680
Our source--
all of a sudden, it's moving.

354
00:17:29,682 --> 00:17:31,816
What kind of
a power source moves?

355
00:17:31,818 --> 00:17:33,518
I'm not sure.

356
00:17:35,555 --> 00:17:36,788
All right, well...

357
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:39,724
Let's see if we can
hone in on it.

358
00:17:44,530 --> 00:17:46,798
Get out of the way!

359
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,067
Man:
We're running out of water!

360
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:58,743
Man:
Let people in!
We need water!

361
00:17:58,745 --> 00:18:00,511
Angie!

362
00:18:00,513 --> 00:18:02,480
Where have you been?
Rose!

363
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:06,651
Are you okay?

364
00:18:06,653 --> 00:18:10,154
Junior, he...

365
00:18:11,690 --> 00:18:15,426
What?
Junior what?

366
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:18,529
The day that the
dome came down,

367
00:18:18,531 --> 00:18:20,631
Junior locked me in
his fallout shelter.

368
00:18:20,633 --> 00:18:21,799
What?!

369
00:18:21,801 --> 00:18:24,335
I tried to escape,
but I couldn't.

370
00:18:24,337 --> 00:18:26,370
And then big jim found me.

371
00:18:26,372 --> 00:18:27,772
And he let you out.

372
00:18:27,774 --> 00:18:30,775
No. He locked me in again.

373
00:18:30,777 --> 00:18:32,677
Big jim did?
And the only reason

374
00:18:32,679 --> 00:18:34,645
He let me out
this morning is because...

375
00:18:34,647 --> 00:18:37,682
He thought this missile
was gonna kill us all.

376
00:18:37,684 --> 00:18:40,818
I can't believe big jim
would do something like that.

377
00:18:40,820 --> 00:18:42,320
Rose, I'm not lying.

378
00:18:42,322 --> 00:18:45,356
When he finally
let me out, I...

379
00:18:45,358 --> 00:18:47,358
I ran.

380
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:51,129
I ran and I ran
to my parents' house.

381
00:18:51,131 --> 00:18:53,397
I couldn't find joe.
Oh...

382
00:18:53,399 --> 00:18:55,466
I couldn't find my brother!
Oh.

383
00:18:55,468 --> 00:18:57,301
Your brother is safe.

384
00:18:57,303 --> 00:18:59,704
And so are you.

385
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:06,477
But junior's a cop now.

386
00:19:06,479 --> 00:19:09,413
And his dad's a councilman.

387
00:19:09,415 --> 00:19:12,683
Who's gonna believe
my word against theirs?

388
00:19:14,786 --> 00:19:16,254
I do.

389
00:19:16,256 --> 00:19:18,422
I do.

390
00:19:19,391 --> 00:19:20,925
Don't you worry, honey,

391
00:19:20,927 --> 00:19:24,328
'cause we'll make sure that
everybody else does, too.

392
00:19:25,564 --> 00:19:27,165
Are you sure a diabetic
lives here?

393
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:28,366
Yeah.

394
00:19:28,368 --> 00:19:30,368
Name's on the medical
files I pulled.

395
00:19:30,370 --> 00:19:31,836
Ray garcia.

396
00:19:31,838 --> 00:19:34,739
341 cupidas drive.

397
00:19:34,741 --> 00:19:36,807
Yeah, well,
no one's home.

398
00:19:37,810 --> 00:19:38,943
Can we come back later?

399
00:19:38,945 --> 00:19:41,379
Joe, we don't want them
to be home.

400
00:19:41,381 --> 00:19:43,915
Plus, maybe they got caught
outside the dome.

401
00:19:55,794 --> 00:19:57,929
Wait, wait, norrie,
we-we can't just...

402
00:20:09,942 --> 00:20:11,609
What are you kids doing?

403
00:20:11,611 --> 00:20:13,611
My mom needs insulin.

404
00:20:13,613 --> 00:20:15,880
So you figured
you'd steal mine?

405
00:20:15,882 --> 00:20:19,684
She's... She's gonna die.

406
00:20:19,686 --> 00:20:22,820
Just like the rest of us.

407
00:20:23,789 --> 00:20:27,558
I took my last dose
yesterday.

408
00:20:29,528 --> 00:20:31,662
Now, go on.

409
00:20:31,664 --> 00:20:35,233
Get out of here before
I blow your damn heads off.

410
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:42,840
they're gonna run out of food!

411
00:20:42,842 --> 00:20:45,476
Let's go! Back up! Move!

412
00:20:45,478 --> 00:20:46,777
Can't wait any longer!

413
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:49,547
Let's go!

414
00:20:49,549 --> 00:20:50,715
No, no, no, no!

415
00:20:50,717 --> 00:20:51,549
Hey, hey, hey,
come on, stop!

416
00:20:55,854 --> 00:20:57,888
Hey!
Stop! Let her go!

417
00:20:57,890 --> 00:20:59,257
No! Get your hands off!

418
00:20:59,259 --> 00:21:01,592
Hey! Get your hands
off that woman!

419
00:21:01,594 --> 00:21:02,660
Go to hell!

420
00:21:06,598 --> 00:21:09,000
Move it! Move it!

421
00:21:32,991 --> 00:21:34,925
Linda:
Barbie!

422
00:21:34,927 --> 00:21:37,862
Barbie... Get ahold
of yourself.

423
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:44,535
Can I count on you?

424
00:21:44,537 --> 00:21:46,537
It won't happen again.

425
00:21:46,539 --> 00:21:49,473
All right, this thing
is starting to spread.

426
00:21:49,475 --> 00:21:50,841
We need to do
something, and fast.

427
00:21:50,843 --> 00:21:51,909
Carter, come with me.

428
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:17,768
What the hell
do you think you're doing?

429
00:22:17,770 --> 00:22:19,103
We know that you still got meat

430
00:22:19,105 --> 00:22:20,638
In that freezer of yours.
Yeah.

431
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:23,574
And it doesn't belong
to either of you.

432
00:22:23,576 --> 00:22:24,975
You don't get
it, rose.

433
00:22:24,977 --> 00:22:26,944
We're stuck in here
with no water.

434
00:22:26,946 --> 00:22:28,779
Food's running out.

435
00:22:28,781 --> 00:22:30,481
A bomb couldn't even
crack that damn thing.

436
00:22:30,483 --> 00:22:33,851
So we're just gonna
take what we want.

437
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:37,655
Right after you kiss my ass!

438
00:22:37,657 --> 00:22:39,924
rose!

439
00:22:41,394 --> 00:22:43,594
Rose!

440
00:22:51,436 --> 00:22:52,937
Rose!

441
00:22:54,907 --> 00:22:57,408
You bastard!

442
00:23:26,139 --> 00:23:28,439
Where have you been?
At the station.

443
00:23:28,441 --> 00:23:30,441
I remembered duke telling me
about some riot gear

444
00:23:30,443 --> 00:23:33,911
The feds sent us
after 9/11.

445
00:23:33,913 --> 00:23:35,813
This is it?
This stuff's...

446
00:23:35,815 --> 00:23:38,949
It's ten years old--
it loses effectiveness.

447
00:23:38,951 --> 00:23:40,851
Get ready to
clear the crowd.

448
00:23:44,956 --> 00:23:47,158
Man: Move out of the way!
Look out!

449
00:23:47,160 --> 00:23:49,193
Run!

450
00:23:52,831 --> 00:23:55,900
Barbie:
The tear gas isn't working.
It's not stopping them.

451
00:24:02,908 --> 00:24:05,042
Dodee:
<i>Slow down, slow down.</i>

452
00:24:05,044 --> 00:24:06,811
Damn it!

453
00:24:06,813 --> 00:24:07,812
Now what?

454
00:24:07,814 --> 00:24:09,113
I lost the signal.

455
00:24:09,115 --> 00:24:10,681
How?

456
00:24:10,683 --> 00:24:11,982
I don't know.
Just-just give me

457
00:24:11,984 --> 00:24:13,150
A second.

458
00:24:13,152 --> 00:24:14,585
Wait, wait, wait,

459
00:24:14,587 --> 00:24:16,020
It's back.
Hurry, hurry, go.
Okay.

460
00:24:16,022 --> 00:24:18,055
We're close.
All right.

461
00:24:21,493 --> 00:24:22,927
Door's unlocked--

462
00:24:22,929 --> 00:24:25,029
It's not like
we're breaking in.

463
00:24:25,031 --> 00:24:28,098
Now say it like
you mean it.

464
00:24:43,048 --> 00:24:44,882
Nore?

465
00:24:48,787 --> 00:24:50,955
What are you
doing here?

466
00:24:50,957 --> 00:24:53,757
We were just... Um...

467
00:24:55,694 --> 00:24:57,528
Where are your parents?

468
00:24:57,530 --> 00:24:59,029
Mom went to the store.

469
00:24:59,031 --> 00:25:02,099
Dad can't get back home with
that dome thing outside.

470
00:25:07,005 --> 00:25:09,540
We're not gonna hurt you.

471
00:25:09,542 --> 00:25:11,942
I'm not scared.

472
00:25:11,944 --> 00:25:14,912
Mom says I'm not a
little boy anymore.

473
00:25:14,914 --> 00:25:17,681
I even do my own shots now.

474
00:25:19,951 --> 00:25:22,086
You have diabetes?

475
00:25:22,088 --> 00:25:24,021
Yeah, but it's
not a big deal.

476
00:25:29,094 --> 00:25:32,029
Take these back
to the fridge.

477
00:25:36,134 --> 00:25:38,702
Wait.

478
00:25:43,108 --> 00:25:45,676
Woman: What the hell
are you doing here?

479
00:25:47,045 --> 00:25:49,780
Get out!

480
00:25:51,683 --> 00:25:54,585
I'm sorry.

481
00:25:54,587 --> 00:25:57,655
That was a stupid idea.
You were right.

482
00:25:57,657 --> 00:26:00,891
Let's just go back
to your mom's.

483
00:26:00,893 --> 00:26:02,126
Julia:
Hey, joe!

484
00:26:02,128 --> 00:26:04,028
What are you guys
doing here?

485
00:26:04,030 --> 00:26:06,664
Uh... We were just...

486
00:26:06,666 --> 00:26:07,965
Out on a walk.

487
00:26:07,967 --> 00:26:09,233
What are you guys doing?

488
00:26:09,235 --> 00:26:11,101
wild goose hunt.

489
00:26:11,103 --> 00:26:13,771
The signal's coming
from right here.

490
00:26:14,974 --> 00:26:16,674
From this house?

491
00:26:18,209 --> 00:26:20,277
I think it's coming from them.

492
00:26:26,117 --> 00:26:28,185
What's this?

493
00:26:28,187 --> 00:26:30,854
It's my end of the deal.

494
00:26:32,123 --> 00:26:34,258
Got what you want, ollie.

495
00:26:34,260 --> 00:26:38,262
So be prepared for town folk
to start coming over,

496
00:26:38,264 --> 00:26:40,664
Getting their water.

497
00:26:40,666 --> 00:26:43,934
Well, it's a good start, anyway.

498
00:26:43,936 --> 00:26:46,370
Need another delivery
about a week from now.

499
00:26:46,372 --> 00:26:48,172
You know, I could always
seize that well,

500
00:26:48,174 --> 00:26:49,773
You backwoods son of a bitch.

501
00:26:49,775 --> 00:26:51,141
And I'm sure
you'd find some bylaw

502
00:26:51,143 --> 00:26:53,310
Or loophole to justify doing it.

503
00:26:53,312 --> 00:26:56,280
I mean, that's always been
the big jim way, hasn't it?

504
00:26:56,282 --> 00:26:58,015
But not anymore.

505
00:26:58,017 --> 00:26:59,116
What's that supposed to mean?

506
00:26:59,118 --> 00:27:01,118
It means I don't give
a rat's ass

507
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:02,953
What piece of official paper
you pull out.

508
00:27:02,955 --> 00:27:05,823
You step foot on my land
except to bring me more propane,

509
00:27:05,825 --> 00:27:07,391
You'll get a bullet
between the eyes.

510
00:27:08,827 --> 00:27:12,329
I always could
shoot better than you.

511
00:27:12,331 --> 00:27:14,164
Be careful, ollie.

512
00:27:14,166 --> 00:27:17,868
Times like this,
you don't want to stand alone.

513
00:27:20,005 --> 00:27:21,672
Cross me.

514
00:27:21,674 --> 00:27:23,907
We'll see who stands where.

515
00:27:30,081 --> 00:27:34,051
yeah, junior's girl
really put up a fight.

516
00:27:34,053 --> 00:27:36,086
She can't now.

517
00:27:39,291 --> 00:27:41,792
Go watch the door, clint.

518
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:46,930
Angie mcalister.

519
00:27:46,932 --> 00:27:50,134
I don't think you're gonna mind.

520
00:28:02,914 --> 00:28:04,882
Joe:
Wait, this is <i>our</i> fault?

521
00:28:04,884 --> 00:28:06,350
So you think
<i>we're</i> what's jammig

522
00:28:06,352 --> 00:28:08,018
All the frequencies
in town?

523
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:10,254
All we know is,
whatever this signal thing is,

524
00:28:10,256 --> 00:28:12,690
It started today
and it led us straight

525
00:28:12,692 --> 00:28:13,691
To you guys.

526
00:28:13,693 --> 00:28:14,792
Yeah, but why today?

527
00:28:14,794 --> 00:28:17,161
I mean, it's not like
we did anything.

528
00:28:17,163 --> 00:28:19,063
I know it doesn't
make any sense.

529
00:28:19,065 --> 00:28:21,298
It sort of does.

530
00:28:21,300 --> 00:28:23,400
We have to tell someone.

531
00:28:23,402 --> 00:28:25,269
Dodee:
Tell us what?

532
00:28:25,271 --> 00:28:27,838
The day the dome came down...

533
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:30,174
We both started having seizures.

534
00:28:30,176 --> 00:28:32,876
All the people
who've seen us seize...

535
00:28:32,878 --> 00:28:35,112
Have said that
we said something.

536
00:28:35,114 --> 00:28:36,847
The exact same thing.

537
00:28:36,849 --> 00:28:39,349
Okay, I'm officially
freaked out.

538
00:28:39,351 --> 00:28:41,285
H-here.

539
00:28:47,292 --> 00:28:49,326
Both: The pink stars
are falling in lines.

540
00:28:49,328 --> 00:28:52,062
The pink stars are falling.

541
00:28:52,064 --> 00:28:54,298
The pink stars
are falling.

542
00:28:54,300 --> 00:28:56,166
The pink stars are
falling in lines.

543
00:28:56,168 --> 00:28:58,836
The pink stars are falling.

544
00:28:58,838 --> 00:29:00,471
The pink stars
are falling.

545
00:29:00,473 --> 00:29:02,206
The pink stars are fall...

546
00:29:04,243 --> 00:29:06,310
Barbie:
Hey! Break it up!

547
00:29:12,851 --> 00:29:15,152
Clint:
Sorry, man, diner's closed.

548
00:29:15,154 --> 00:29:17,454
When did rose
make you the doorman?

549
00:29:18,457 --> 00:29:19,890
Rose?
Yeah.

550
00:29:19,892 --> 00:29:21,959
Waylon! Get
out of there!

551
00:29:28,233 --> 00:29:29,366
Hey!

552
00:30:00,299 --> 00:30:02,432
What happened?

553
00:30:03,201 --> 00:30:05,335
Rose is dead.

554
00:30:06,304 --> 00:30:08,806
Rose?

555
00:30:08,808 --> 00:30:09,807
Oh, my god.

556
00:30:09,809 --> 00:30:11,074
I need your keys.

557
00:30:11,076 --> 00:30:13,577
I got to get her
to the clinic.

558
00:30:19,350 --> 00:30:20,317
Linda:
Damn it.

559
00:30:20,319 --> 00:30:22,319
Someone slashed the tires.

560
00:30:26,024 --> 00:30:28,425
It's time for
rule number two.

561
00:30:31,062 --> 00:30:33,497
Stop. Stop!

562
00:30:52,417 --> 00:30:54,218
Man:
It can rain!

563
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:56,220
It can rain inside the dome!

564
00:30:59,024 --> 00:31:00,924
All right!

565
00:31:00,926 --> 00:31:03,560
Don't just stand there, folks,
grab a bucket, grab a trash can!

566
00:31:03,562 --> 00:31:06,363
We need to save every drop
we can! Now, come on!

567
00:31:17,609 --> 00:31:19,910
Hey, I got to get her
to the clinic.

568
00:31:19,912 --> 00:31:23,480
Is that angie mcalister?
What happened?

569
00:31:23,482 --> 00:31:24,648
Barbie: Looters.
They broke in

570
00:31:24,650 --> 00:31:26,350
To the diner, they
knocked her out.

571
00:31:28,620 --> 00:31:32,289
And rose...

572
00:31:32,291 --> 00:31:34,658
What about rose?

573
00:31:34,660 --> 00:31:36,960
She's dead.

574
00:31:38,930 --> 00:31:40,964
These two guys.

575
00:31:40,966 --> 00:31:43,433
One kept calling
the other one... Waylon?

576
00:31:43,435 --> 00:31:45,669
Sounds like the dundee brothers.

577
00:31:53,011 --> 00:31:54,912
Find them.

578
00:32:18,069 --> 00:32:21,204
Dome's still here.

579
00:32:21,206 --> 00:32:23,540
Outside it's totally dry.

580
00:32:23,542 --> 00:32:25,709
How is it only raining in here?

581
00:32:25,711 --> 00:32:28,111
The dome must have
its own microclimate.

582
00:32:28,113 --> 00:32:30,213
The water from
the lake evaporates,

583
00:32:30,215 --> 00:32:32,549
But the dome traps it inside.

584
00:32:32,551 --> 00:32:35,385
But the beautiful thing
about the evaporation process

585
00:32:35,387 --> 00:32:39,089
Is it filters the water
so you can drink it.

586
00:32:39,091 --> 00:32:41,725
Guess we're not gonna run out
of water after all.

587
00:32:41,727 --> 00:32:43,093
Yeah, great.

588
00:32:43,095 --> 00:32:45,162
So now we can spend
the rest of our lives

589
00:32:45,164 --> 00:32:47,230
Inside this damn thing.

590
00:32:49,567 --> 00:32:51,568
whoa!

591
00:32:55,707 --> 00:32:57,541
Radio's working again.

592
00:32:57,543 --> 00:33:00,210
Whatever was jamming
the airwaves is gone.

593
00:33:04,115 --> 00:33:07,284
That's because joe and norrie
touched the dome together.

594
00:33:07,286 --> 00:33:09,286
What the hell
does that mean?

595
00:33:09,288 --> 00:33:12,422
You know what,
I don't have time for this.

596
00:33:12,424 --> 00:33:14,191
I've got to get to my mom.

597
00:33:14,193 --> 00:33:15,292
I'll drive you.

598
00:33:15,294 --> 00:33:17,227
No. The clinic's not far.

599
00:33:17,229 --> 00:33:18,228
I'll walk.

600
00:33:18,230 --> 00:33:20,063
You come with.

601
00:33:28,539 --> 00:33:31,174
They're connected to it.

602
00:33:31,176 --> 00:33:33,777
It's like the dome is...

603
00:33:33,779 --> 00:33:36,046
Using them.

604
00:33:37,749 --> 00:33:39,249
Okay.

605
00:33:39,251 --> 00:33:40,717
How?

606
00:33:40,719 --> 00:33:43,754
I don't know yet.

607
00:33:43,756 --> 00:33:46,523
We could have died today
in that missile strike.

608
00:33:46,525 --> 00:33:50,160
And instead, the dome
ended up protecting us.

609
00:33:50,162 --> 00:33:51,695
And just when we need water...

610
00:33:51,697 --> 00:33:53,497
It rains.

611
00:33:53,499 --> 00:33:56,533
I mean, this can't
just be a coincidence.

612
00:33:56,535 --> 00:33:59,436
Okay, so what,
now the dome's helping us?

613
00:33:59,438 --> 00:34:01,204
Maybe.

614
00:34:05,743 --> 00:34:10,147
Maybe it's trying
to reassure us.

615
00:34:10,149 --> 00:34:13,283
First it traps us...

616
00:34:13,285 --> 00:34:16,653
Now it's trying to reassure us.

617
00:34:16,655 --> 00:34:18,221
No.

618
00:34:18,223 --> 00:34:21,324
No, there's nothing warm
and fuzzy about this, julia.

619
00:34:21,326 --> 00:34:24,628
And we need to tell someone
about <i>them.</i>

620
00:34:27,231 --> 00:34:29,199
Big jim's gonna know what to do.

621
00:34:29,201 --> 00:34:30,734
Do you have any idea

622
00:34:30,736 --> 00:34:33,737
What will happen if word
gets out about those kids?

623
00:34:33,739 --> 00:34:36,773
The whole town
will be after them.

624
00:34:36,775 --> 00:34:41,178
Until we know what this is,
we can't tell anyone.

625
00:34:46,250 --> 00:34:47,818
Fine.

626
00:34:49,720 --> 00:34:51,254
For now.

627
00:35:22,753 --> 00:35:26,823
Carolyn: I don't know how
you guys came up with this...

628
00:35:28,693 --> 00:35:30,727
...But I'm glad you did.

629
00:35:32,830 --> 00:35:36,266
When she needs
her next dose?

630
00:35:38,236 --> 00:35:42,772
Let's just be happy
she's better for now.

631
00:35:42,774 --> 00:35:44,441
Okay.

632
00:35:44,443 --> 00:35:46,676
♪

633
00:36:10,701 --> 00:36:12,702
Barbie.

634
00:36:12,704 --> 00:36:15,705
I've been
looking for you.

635
00:36:15,707 --> 00:36:18,909
You okay?

636
00:36:18,911 --> 00:36:20,443
Yeah.

637
00:36:20,445 --> 00:36:22,879
You okay?

638
00:36:22,881 --> 00:36:25,448
Yeah. It's, uh...

639
00:36:25,450 --> 00:36:28,218
It's been a hell
of a crazy day.

640
00:36:28,220 --> 00:36:29,719
Yeah, I guess you could say

641
00:36:29,721 --> 00:36:32,389
Everybody went
a little crazy today.

642
00:36:39,530 --> 00:36:41,631
We're gonna be okay.

643
00:37:20,706 --> 00:37:21,871
Hello?

644
00:37:21,873 --> 00:37:23,873
Big jim: I'd take it
easy if I were you.

645
00:37:27,913 --> 00:37:30,981
What...

646
00:37:32,950 --> 00:37:34,851
What is going on?

647
00:37:34,853 --> 00:37:37,787
Barbie found you knocked
out in the diner.

648
00:37:37,789 --> 00:37:40,490
Rose...

649
00:37:40,492 --> 00:37:42,993
She needs help.

650
00:37:42,995 --> 00:37:45,962
I'm, uh, I'm afraid
it's too late.

651
00:37:51,636 --> 00:37:54,604
She was a good friend to me.

652
00:38:00,544 --> 00:38:02,946
What...

653
00:38:02,948 --> 00:38:06,283
What am I doing here?

654
00:38:07,885 --> 00:38:09,886
You can't lock me up again.

655
00:38:09,888 --> 00:38:12,589
No, no, the front door's open;
you can leave anytime you like.

656
00:38:13,924 --> 00:38:15,759
Though I was

657
00:38:15,761 --> 00:38:18,395
Hoping...

658
00:38:18,397 --> 00:38:22,766
That you and I could...
Come to an arrangement.

659
00:38:26,437 --> 00:38:28,872
Junior kidnapped me.

660
00:38:28,874 --> 00:38:31,074
No amount of money
can pay for that.

661
00:38:31,076 --> 00:38:35,011
You'll get no
argument from me.

662
00:38:35,013 --> 00:38:37,947
You know, deep down...

663
00:38:37,949 --> 00:38:41,318
I think I always knew
something was off...

664
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:43,720
With my son.

665
00:38:43,722 --> 00:38:45,822
Ever since his mom died.

666
00:38:47,758 --> 00:38:49,859
I guess I just...

667
00:38:49,861 --> 00:38:52,028
Couldn't admit
it to myself.

668
00:38:52,997 --> 00:38:55,098
So I'm not talking about

669
00:38:55,100 --> 00:38:58,501
Giving you money.

670
00:38:58,503 --> 00:39:01,805
I'm offering you my word.

671
00:39:01,807 --> 00:39:03,940
Your word?

672
00:39:03,942 --> 00:39:08,078
Junior rennie will never touch
you again; I'll make sure of it.

673
00:39:11,082 --> 00:39:14,017
And, uh, well, I mean, if...

674
00:39:14,019 --> 00:39:17,020
If you <i>need</i> money...

675
00:39:17,022 --> 00:39:19,989
Or... What counts as money

676
00:39:19,991 --> 00:39:23,126
In town these days--
you know, propane,

677
00:39:23,128 --> 00:39:25,428
Food, water,

678
00:39:25,430 --> 00:39:28,832
A gun--

679
00:39:28,834 --> 00:39:31,801
Well, you'll have it.

680
00:39:31,803 --> 00:39:33,803
If you will just try to

681
00:39:33,805 --> 00:39:37,407
Put this terrible event
behind you...

682
00:39:39,009 --> 00:39:43,680
...I'll get you anything
your little heart desires.

683
00:39:46,984 --> 00:39:48,852
What about joe?

684
00:39:48,854 --> 00:39:52,055
I need to know that my brother
will be taken care of, too.

685
00:39:52,057 --> 00:39:55,158
Done.

686
00:39:55,160 --> 00:39:57,026
We can be friends.

687
00:40:00,164 --> 00:40:03,666
And, uh...

688
00:40:03,668 --> 00:40:05,869
Trust me,

689
00:40:05,871 --> 00:40:07,971
Times like these,

690
00:40:07,973 --> 00:40:10,039
It's good to have
a friend like...

691
00:40:10,041 --> 00:40:12,108
Big jim rennie.

692
00:40:14,178 --> 00:40:16,146
I don't know.

693
00:40:17,481 --> 00:40:18,982
I have to think about it.

694
00:40:21,420 --> 00:40:23,420
Dad.

695
00:40:26,090 --> 00:40:28,124
Angie.

696
00:40:30,628 --> 00:40:32,929
What's going on here?

